==Roosevelt Hall==
Roosevelt Hall (built 1903–1907) is a Beaux Arts–style building housing the NWC since its inception in 1946. Designed by the New York architectural firm McKim, Mead &amp; White, it is now designated a National Historic Landmark. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.

